dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Samuels b Russell 69 (109b 2x4 1x6 157m) SR: 63.3

dismissalComment.html: caught at deep square leg! Russell banged the ball in short and Mushfiqur pulled it, hitting it straight to Samuels, who didn't have to move very much to take the catch. Mirpur began to cheer at first when he hit the shot, and then fell silent

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Hossain b Sammy 50 (54b 3x4 1x6 79m) SR: 92.59

dismissalComment.html: bowled! Nasir charged Sammy but was confronted by a slower delivery, he couldn't cope with the change of pace and missed a straight ball. He's played a superb innings to take Bangladesh past 200

Lendl Simmons lbw b Shakib Al Hasan 80 (125b 3x4 3x6 141m) SR: 64

dismissalComment.html: lbw! Simmons tried to sweep again but didn't make contact. He had taken a long stride forward but the ball pitched in line and went straight on to hit the front pad. He misses a second century but has done more than enough to win this game

headshotImage.caption: Danza Hyatt player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Danza Hyatt player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: Has that been caught at long-off? Hyatt hit the ball flat and hard towards long-off, Rubel Hossain came running in from the boundary and dived forward, catching it centimetres before it hit the turf. He stays motionless on the ground for a few moments before raising his finger, indicating it's out. The umpires refer it to the third umpire. It's a clean catch though, and Hyatt has to go. The delivery was tossed up slower and Hyatt didn't get to its pitch as he cleared his front foot to attack

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: played off the pads to square leg and a quick single seals the series for West Indies. They lead 2-0 with one to play

commentPostTextItems.html: 8.40 pm West Indies have chased this with ridiculous ease. At no stage did they face any problems. Simmons and Hyatt began with a solid first-wicket stand, and them Samuels and Simmons finished the job. Bangladesh were dispirited in the field and just going through the motions.

Bangladesh, however, lost the game when they batted. The contest was up as early as the second over, when they were reduced to 1 for 3. Even though Mushfiqur and the lower-middle order rallied, it was largely game over.
Mushfiqur: "On that flat wicket we chose to bat, but 20 for 4 ... the lower order showed character. Our top-order batsman took the easy option ... we need to work hard for the next match."
The Man of the Match is Marlon Samuels, one wicket and plenty of eye-catching runs. Well deserved. That's it from us at ESPNcricinfo for today. See you next time. Cheers.

Sammy: "The previous few games we've put in a professional display. It was an all-round team effort. The wickets have been good one-day wickets ... the way we went about our job, the bowlers stuck to their plan and the batsmen are taking responsibility."

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammad Ashraful c Sammy b Roach 0 (5b 0x4 0x6 5m) SR: 0

dismissalComment.html: caught at second slip! Ashraful pokes at a length ball outside off stump, again the delivery isn't special, the edge flies to Sammy who juggles the first attempt and takes it on the second

dismissalText.commentary: Shakib Al Hasan c †Ramdin b Rampaul 12 (9b 3x4 0x6 11m) SR: 133.33

dismissalComment.html: caught behind again! Shakib plays a poor shot after hitting three fours in the previous over. He barely moves his feet and drives away from his body at a length ball angling across him from over the wicket, gets an edge to Ramdin

dismissalText.commentary: Alok Kapali c Simmons b Roach 20 (43b 3x4 0x6 62m) SR: 46.51

dismissalComment.html: caught at midwicket! After initially struggling against the short ball and then settling in, Kapali finally falls to one. Roach banged it in and Kapali pulled. The ball was a bit quicker and Kapali skied it high in the air and was caught by Simmons on the edge of the circle. He tumbled to the ground as he took it

dismissalText.commentary: Naeem Islam c & b Samuels 30 (42b 3x4 0x6 44m) SR: 71.42

dismissalComment.html: caught and bowled! Naeem moves forward and simply chips the ball straight to the bowler. That's one of the easiest caught and bowled chances Samuels will get

dismissalText.commentary: Mushfiqur Rahim c Samuels b Russell 69 (109b 2x4 1x6 157m) SR: 63.3

dismissalComment.html: caught at deep square leg! Russell banged the ball in short and Mushfiqur pulled it, hitting it straight to Samuels, who didn't have to move very much to take the catch. Mirpur began to cheer at first when he hit the shot, and then fell silent

dismissalText.commentary: Abdur Razzak run out (Russell) 25 (19b 3x4 1x6 28m) SR: 131.57

dismissalComment.html: huge blow for Bangladesh, Razzak is run out! Nasir pushed the ball towards midwicket, Razzak wanted the strike and set off for the single. Nasir sent him back but before Razzak could regain his ground, Andre Russell swooped on the ball and hit the stumps direct at the bowler's end

dismissalText.commentary: Shafiul Islam c Bishoo b Sammy 4 (6b 0x4 0x6 13m) SR: 66.66

dismissalComment.html: fuller length around off stump, Shafiul slogs, aiming for the long-on boundary. He skies the ball in the air towards cover and Bishoo takes the catch

dismissalText.commentary: Nasir Hossain b Sammy 50 (54b 3x4 1x6 79m) SR: 92.59

dismissalComment.html: bowled! Nasir charged Sammy but was confronted by a slower delivery, he couldn't cope with the change of pace and missed a straight ball. He's played a superb innings to take Bangladesh past 200

dismissalText.commentary: Lendl Simmons lbw b Shakib Al Hasan 80 (125b 3x4 3x6 141m) SR: 64

dismissalComment.html: lbw! Simmons tried to sweep again but didn't make contact. He had taken a long stride forward but the ball pitched in line and went straight on to hit the front pad. He misses a second century but has done more than enough to win this game

dismissalText.long: c Rubel Hossain b Shakib Al Hasan
dismissalText.commentary: Danza Hyatt c Rubel Hossain b Shakib Al Hasan 39 (46b 2x4 4x6 59m) SR: 84.78

dismissalComment.html: Has that been caught at long-off? Hyatt hit the ball flat and hard towards long-off, Rubel Hossain came running in from the boundary and dived forward, catching it centimetres before it hit the turf. He stays motionless on the ground for a few moments before raising his finger, indicating it's out. The umpires refer it to the third umpire. It's a clean catch though, and Hyatt has to go. The delivery was tossed up slower and Hyatt didn't get to its pitch as he cleared his front foot to attack

dismissalText.commentary: Marlon Samuels not out 88 (74b 12x4 1x6 102m) SR: 118.91
Darren Bravo not out 1 (12b 0x4 0x6 21m) SR: 8.33
